comment.author: 22251505@N04
comment._content: The aeroplane could easily be a Curtis Jenny. Tailplane shape, struts and fin all look like one. Although the wing is severly broken up, there are braced struts which were a charicteristic of the top wing of the Jenny. The roundel is well inboard which the US AC used in WW1.
